MyBroadband’s latest speed test results show that Audatex has the highest peak Internet speed for local companies, followed by FNB and Flight Centre. MyBroadband’s new HTML 5 speed test servers are hosted in Teraco’s vendor-neutral data centres to ensure a neutral testing environment. Through NAPAfrica, all network operators present at its peering points are provided with a free 1Gbps connection to the MyBroadband speed test platform. The new MyBroadband speed test platform was designed to be lightweight and easy to use on mobile devices. Over 55,000 speed tests have been conducted on the new MyBroadband speed test platform since it was launched in March. The speed test results showed that the company with the highest peak Internet speed was Audatex, with a peak speed of 919Mbps. FNB ranked second with a download speed of 742Mbps, and Flight Centre third with 709Mbps. The table below shows the peak Internet speeds at prominent companies in South Africa. It should be noted that only companies with their own IP ranges are listed below.